"true\" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_3540467\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_3540467\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 22, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104eka1665703524971.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/eka1665703524971.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/eka1665703524971.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"eka1665703524971\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Add, remove, or edit multiple breakpoints at specific locations in your ProcScript\n      modules.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"eka1665703524971__p_d175199e1_d175200e1_d175201e1\">You can also specify conditional breakpoints, which means that the application should break only if a certain condition occurs.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"eka1665703524971__section_c4y_bvh_1xb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d996072e57\">Editing breakpoints</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">Refer to <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yyl1665703525402.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yyl1665703525402.html\" title=\"Displays the contents of the ProcScript module for the item selected in the Structure field.\">Trigger / Module</a> when editing breakpoints.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"eka1665703524971__section_ykc_ysh_1xb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d996072e76\">ProcScript Module and Line</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">Refer to the following topics:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"eka1665703524971__ul_aqr_ysh_1xb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"eka1665703524971__li_d53366e1_d53367e1_d53368e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yhe1665702860098.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yhe1665702860098.html\" title=\"Name of the ProcScript module.\">ProcScript Module for breakpoints</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"eka1665703524971__li_d53369e1_d53370e1_d53371e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fil1665702860168.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fil1665702860168.html\" title=\"ProcScript module line number where the breakpoint is located.\">ProcScript Line for breakpoints</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"eka1665703524971__section_kvr_kth_1xb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d996072e108\">Location list</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">The <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Location</span> list displays the structure name, ProcScript module\n            name, and line number of breakpoints.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"eka1665703524971__section_lbb_4th_1xb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d996072e120\">Structure</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">Specifiy the name of the component or global ProcScript that contains the\n            breakpoint.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"eka1665703524971__p_d175229e1_d175230e1_d175231e1\">If you are adding a new breakpoint, enter the name\n            of the structure in which to set the breakpoint.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"eka1665703524971__section_hc3_tth_1xb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d996072e133\">Types</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">For a new breakpoint, select a component or global ProcScript from the drop-down\n            list.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"eka1665703524971__p_d175280e1_d175281e1_d175282e1\">The selected value must be consistent with the\n               <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Structure</span> name field. That is, if you choose\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">Component</code>, the <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Structure</span> name should be the\n            name of a component.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"eka1665703524971__section_y1b_vth_1xb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d996072e154\">Conditions</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">Specify a conditional expression that can be handled by the\n               <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$condition</span> ProcScript function.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"eka1665703524971__p_d175295e1_d175296e1_d175297e1\">If you want the breakpoint to occur only if a\n            specific condition occurs, enter a conditional expression. For example,\n               <code class=\"ph codeph\">$status=-1</code>, or <code class=\"ph codeph\">$procerror=-11</code>, or any other\n            condition that evaluates to TRUE or FALSE.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"eka1665703524971__p_d175298e1_d175299e1_d175300e1\">The debugger does not compile the conditional\n            expression, so you cannot use compile time constants, including ProcScript error\n            constants. You must enter literal values, such as the -1 and -11 in the preceding\n            example. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fzj1665702782147.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fzj1665702782147.html\" title=\"Return the result of evaluating a conditional expression.\">$condition</a>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"eka1665703524971__section_unm_z5h_1xb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d996072e185\">Buttons</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">Use the breakpoint buttons, which include:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"eka1665703524971__ul_vnm_z5h_1xb\">\n<li class=\"li\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Remove</span>—remove the breakpoint highlighted in the\n                  <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Location</span> list. </li>\n<li class=\"li\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Add</span>—add a new breakpoint as specified in the\n                  <span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Details</span> fields. </li>\n<li class=\"li\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">OK</span>—accept the modifications you have made using this form </li>\n<li class=\"li\">\n<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Cancel</span>—exit this form without applying the changes. </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ayx1665702860536.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Breakpoints</a><p>A breakpoint is a marked code line, trigger, error, exception, or condition that forces the application or component to break and the debugger to take control of execution.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3540467\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3540467\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Managing breakpoints Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 22, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Add, remove, or edit multiple breakpoints at specific locations in your ProcScript modules. You can also specify conditional breakpoints, which means that the application should break only if a certain condition occurs. Editing breakpoints Refer to Trigger / Module when editing breakpoints. ProcScript Module and Line Refer to the following topics: ProcScript Module for breakpoints ProcScript Line for breakpoints Location list The Location list displays the structure name, ProcScript module name, and line number of breakpoints. Structure Specifiy the name of the component or global ProcScript that contains the breakpoint. If you are adding a new breakpoint, enter the name of the structure in which to set the breakpoint. Types For a new breakpoint, select a component or global ProcScript from the drop-down list. The selected value must be consistent with the Structure name field. That is, if you choose Component , the Structure name should be the name of a component. Conditions Specify a conditional expression that can be handled by the $condition ProcScript function. If you want the breakpoint to occur only if a specific condition occurs, enter a conditional expression. For example, $status=-1 , or $procerror=-11 , or any other condition that evaluates to TRUE or FALSE. The debugger does not compile the conditional expression, so you cannot use compile time constants, including ProcScript error constants. You must enter literal values, such as the -1 and -11 in the preceding example. For more information, see $condition . Buttons Use the breakpoint buttons, which include: Remove —remove the breakpoint highlighted in the Location list. Add —add a new breakpoint as specified in the Details fields. OK —accept the modifications you have made using this form Cancel —exit this form without applying the changes. Related Links Breakpoints A breakpoint is a marked code line, trigger, error, exception, or condition that forces the application or component to break and the debugger to take control of execution. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}